frameDefinitions: A Device or machine is in (or out of) service.
This frame concerns a Perceiver's state of readiness to process and consider impressions of a Figure within a Ground.
An Agent is described as pursuing an Activity, expending some effort.
An Entity exists at a particular Location, at a particular Time, as observed by an implicit observer.
A Rider is being transported in a Vehicle, or is moving on foot.
frameExamples: Legislator tells consumers to be <t>alert</t> to dioxin levels.
Sky, a Korean War veteran, was <t>active</t> in his opposition to Vietnam and continues to protest current combat in Iraq.
Liquid water was <t>present</t> on the surface of Mars billions of years ago.
<t>Mounted</t> police officers are a common sight in this village.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Device</fen> or machine that is in or out of operation.
The <fen>Time</fen> when a <fen>Device</fen> is in or out of operation.
The <fen>Place</fen> in which the <fen>Device</fen> is or is not operating.
The individual that pays attention to the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The entity that the <fen>Perceiver</fen> is specifically focussing on within the <fen>Ground</fen>.
An entity (or event) associated with a <fen>Perceiver</fen> that gives evidence for a <fen>Perceiver</fen>'s attentiveness.
This role identifies the name of the ongoing <fen>Activity</fen> in which an <fen>Agent</fen> engages.
An entity acted upon by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
This role identifies the role filled by the <fen>Agent</fen> which is saliently associated with an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> is pursued.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the  <fen>Activity</fen> is pursued.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose existence at the <fen>Location</fen> is confirmed.
The <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Entity</fen>. The <fen>Location</fen> is conceived as a ground for an event of inspection to determine the presense of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Entity</fen> is present at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Rider</fen> is being transported by a <fen>Vehicle</fen>.
